The paper discusses the development of perceptive abilities in an autonomous robot through interaction with its environment, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach is based on sensorimotor contingencies theory, which is a concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the approach is focused on the discovery of a visual field, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves capturing sensorimotor regularities, which can be modeled using neural networks (cs.NE) or machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
